parameters: "Good morning. Hurry up, the bell is about to ring."
"Oh, good morning. Yesterday was quite the ordeal, huh?"
"No, it wasn't a serious injury, so I'm fine."

"Hahaha, that's reassuring. Then you'll be fine with the
next PE class being extra tough, right?"

"Oh, good morning. Are you coming to school alone again
today?"

"Don't tell me you had a fight with Asahi? Make up with her
quickly!"

(I don't need to be told... I'll make up with her right
away.)

"Haa... Haa... You were so beautiful today as well, Makoto-
sama..."

(Makoto's fans aren't just in this school... I wonder how
many fans she has in this town.)

"You were beautiful as always today, Makoto-sama... But, you
seemed a bit out of spirits..."

(Makoto seemed down, huh. Maybe I shouldn't have said
something so thoughtless.)

"Damn... If only I were a bit smarter... I could pay money
now... for backdoor admission..."

"(Is this girl also a young lady from somewhere... Backdoor
admission... She can't be serious, right...?)"

"Fufufufufu. I've arranged for the money with my father...
now all that's left is to talk to the principal here..."

(Is this person seriously planning to get in through the
back door!?)

"Makoto-sama Makoto-sama Makoto-sama Makoto-sama Makoto-
sama... Makoto-sama Makoto-sama Makoto-sama Makoto-sama
Makoto-sama Makoto-sama Makoto-sama Makoto-sama..."

"(Yikes... That person's dangerous. I'd better not get too
close.)"

"Makoto-sama Makoto-sama Makoto-sama Makoto-sama Makoto-
sama... Makoto-sama Makoto-sama Makoto-sama Makoto-sama
Makoto-sama Makoto-sama Makoto-sama Makoto-sama..."
"(Ah, this person is as relentless as ever...)"

"It's strange, isn't it~. Lady Makoto hasn't shown up no
matter how long we wait."

"She's not someone who would be late... Could something have
happened...?"

"(Makoto still hasn't come to school? That's odd. She wasn't
in front of her house either...)"
(He seems like a scary person. I better not get too close.)

"Oh, the red car that was parked here is gone. It wasn't
just this morning, I saw it during lunch break too."

"There was a suspicious person nearby, and since this school
has many rich students, I have a bad feeling about this. I
hope it's just needless worry."

"(A suspicious man... Considering what happened yesterday,
it is a bit concerning...)"

"(Makoto went home early, but I wonder if she's okay...?
She's probably with her entourage, so no need to worry...?)"

Because of Makoto's immense popularity among the
schoolgirls, once she arrives at school, her entourage
becomes a wall, making it extremely difficult to approach
her.

Perhaps due to the school's prestigious reputation, there
are many young ladies here, and charmed by Makoto's handsome
looks, they began treating her like a \c[10]prince\c[0].

Even from my perspective, Makoto is handsome, and it's a
fair result, but it's tough only being able to talk to her
in the morning after all the effort I put into getting into
the same school.

I really want to spend breaks with Makoto, and I want to eat
lunch together every day. After all, when you're in love
with someone, you want to be with them every second you can.

Yes, embarrassingly enough, I am in love with Makoto. I
haven't found the right moment to confess, but I hope
someday I can.

But she's far out of my league, and there's no way a plain
guy like me could match up with the school's prince. So I
keep these feelings to myself, always locked away in my
heart.

"Hey, everyone, good morning. Were you waiting here for me
again today? We're at the same school, so we could meet
anytime if you wanted."

"We want to chat with Lady Makoto as soon as possible! We
can't just wait in the classroom!"

"That's right! That's right! We'd even like to pick you up
from your home if we could!"

"Oh dear, have you forgotten already!? Picking her up from
home has been strictly forbidden by Lady Makoto herself!"

"That's exactly why we wait for Lady Makoto at the school
gates every morning! Come now, Lady Makoto! Let's go check
out the class assignments together"

"...Well then, Mamoru, see you later. Come on, everyone,
let's go! I hope we're in the same class again this year!"

"Sigh... she's gone... I guess I'll head to the classroom
too..."

"No way~! Even though it's Monday, we can't spend after-
school time together~?"

"Sorry. It looks like I won't be able to hang out for a
while. A friend asked me for a little help."

"Oh my, Makoto-sama is going to help out personally! What
exactly will you be doing?"

"Ah, well... it's nothing major, you know? I'm going to...
teach martial arts to some kids."

"Makoto-sama is going to personally teach martial arts!? I'm
so jealous! I wish I could join~!"

"No, that's not possible! It would be terrible if you got
hurt! Besides, look! Violence doesn't suit delicate maidens
like you!"
"You're making me blush... My face is turning red..."

"Anyway, that's why I can't play with you for a while,
but... you can bear it for me, right?"

"Heh, hehe. Good girls. I'm in a hurry, so!! See you
tomorrow!! Bye!!"

(Teaching martial arts to kids? I haven't heard a single
word about that from Makoto.)

(And Makoto's attitude just now was clearly off. She would
never say such affected things normally...)

(It's like she was acting just to get her followers to
listen to her...)

(I've got a strange feeling about this. It's a bit stalker-
ish, but I think I'll follow Makoto.)

(Makoto definitely went this way. I need to hurry and follow
before I lose sight of her.)

"Ah... I just finished now... No, I don't need a pick-up...
I'd rather not stand out too much."
"Tch... I know... I won't run away... I'll go properly..."

"The place is... go straight ahead and then it's a left,
right? Got it... Ah... I'm going to hang up now."

(I might have never seen Makoto looking so grumpy before.
And just now, it seemed like she clicked her tongue at the
person on the phone...)

"She looked gloomy even while on the call, something seems
off... Could it be that Suzuki is involved again?"

(Maybe I should follow Makoto... If there's nothing wrong,
then that's fine, but if there's something, I have to
help...)

"She looked gloomy even while on the call, something seems
off... Maybe she's gotten involved in something bad."

(Maybe I'll follow Makoto for a bit... If there's nothing
wrong, then that's fine, but if there's something, I have to
help...)

"Alright, I'll start following Makoto right away. I have to
be careful not to be spotted by her."

(I've ended up doing nothing again after school... Can we
really make up at this rate? Hm?)

"Whoa. It was clear until just now, but it's pouring rain.
The weather forecast said it would be sunny all day today."

(I didn't bring a folding umbrella, so I have no choice.
Should I use my bag as a makeshift umbrella and run home?)

"That's the message from the young master. If there's
anything you don't understand, call the usual number."

"I got it... I got it, so... please go somewhere else before
someone sees us..."

"Damn it... He could have just called like he usually does,
but he had to do something that draws attention on
purpose..."

"Sigh... Getting angry won't help. I need to get going
too..."

(That man with the sunglasses... No doubt about it! He's the
same person I saw at Suzuki's house!)

(I couldn't hear what they were talking about because of the
rain, but it must be... no, it's definitely something to do
with Suzuki...)

(If she's planning to meet Suzuki alone, it's far too
dangerous! I have to stop Makoto... I'll follow her!)

"I thought about it until after school, but in the end, I
couldn't come up with a good idea..."

"(At times like this, Makoto would have solved it right
away. Sigh... If only I were as smart as her...)"

"...There's no use brooding over it here. For now, I'll
continue thinking about it when I get home."

"Huh, Makoto? What are you doing here? It doesn't seem like
your fans are around..."

"That... I was concerned about the umbrella you mentioned
this morning. So, um, if it's okay with you, maybe we could
go check it out now?"

"Eh? Don't tell me, you've been waiting for me? Here, all
this time, for me?"

"We-well... I guess that's one way to put it. So, what do
you say? Shall we go to the department store now?"

"I-I'm fine with that! But are you sure? What about your
fans, or any after-school commitments?"

"Right now, I just feel like spending the afternoon with...
with you, Mamoru. Come on, we should hurry before my fans
spot me! Let's go!"

And so, we went to the department store in the downtown
area, and since we were there, we looked around at various
things together. Before we knew it, we had completely
forgotten our original purpose and were just playing around.

By the time we remembered what we came for, it was already
completely dark outside. "We came to pick an umbrella, but
ended up looking at everything else," Makoto said with a
cute smile.

That day, we decided to just go home, and we planned to
visit the department store again another day. But the next
day, just like before, we forgot all about the umbrella and
got carried away having fun.

The initial purpose of looking for an umbrella had somehow
become an excuse for the two of us to hang out. In the end,
we never went to the intended store and continued to play
with Makoto every day.

I really should have asked about various things concerning
Suzuki, but I felt that the moment I asked, this fun time
would end, so I never brought it up until the long holiday
arrived.

Before, I used to say goodbye to Makoto at the school gates,
but ever since we started dating, she quit being everyone's
prince and began to prioritize our time together above all
else.

Many fans, including her entourage, seemed very dissatisfied
at first. But after seeing Makoto's happy face, they
couldn't say anything and accepted our relationship, saying
if Makoto-sama is happy, then it's okay.

I can talk to Makoto anytime in the classroom. We can eat
lunch together every day. The daily life I had imagined
before entering school has finally become a reality.

By the way, that delinquent who brought us together in the
first place has now moved away from this town and is said to
be busily working in an old warehouse.

"I really don't want to go to school on my precious day
off..."

"I really don't want to go to school on my precious day

"I don't want to go to school on my precious day off..."
